709221f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 118th Street
709221f-a.text:
Fifth Avenue (left), at the N.E. corncr of
East 118th Street (foreground), showing rural conditions
prevailing on a rocky ridge on the north side of 118th
Street. To the left is the Avenue and Mt. Morris Park
at 120th Street.
The row of 3-story dwellings at the right are
on the south side of 119th Street and extend to Madison
Avenue. See View 2 for this thoroughfare.
This photo was verified with the photographers
successors (H. N. Tiemann \& Co., No. 176 Lexington Avenue)
and checked with their records of which this is No. 116.
1891
H. N. Tiemann, Photo
Gift of Urbrock Colloction

715182f-a.title: Manhattan: 118th Street (West) - 5th Avenue
715182f-a.text:
23.25 wwst 118th Street, north side, between Fifth and Lenox Aves.
The view shows a synagogue at this site, named Shdarei 2edek.
July 28, 1932.
P Lo Sperr.
